3) App settings you’ll need

Add these to local.settings.json (dev) and Function App → Configuration (prod):

{
  "IsEncrypted": false,
  "Values": {
    "FUNCTIONS_WORKER_RUNTIME": "java",
    "AzureWebJobsStorage": "<storage-conn-string>",

    "ServiceBusConnection": "Endpoint=sb://<ns>.servicebus.windows.net/;SharedAccessKeyName=<send>;SharedAccessKey=<key>",
    "ServiceBusEntity": "neo-events-queue",

    "MESSAGE_API_URL": "https://<your-message-api>/notify",
    "MESSAGE_API_METHOD": "POST",
    "MESSAGE_API_TIMEOUT_SEC": "15",
    "MESSAGE_API_CONNECT_TIMEOUT_SEC": "10",

    // Optional auth
    "MESSAGE_API_AUTH_BEARER": "",
    "MESSAGE_API_KEY_HEADER": "X-API-Key",
    "MESSAGE_API_KEY_VALUE": "",

    // Retry choice on 4xx (besides 408/429)
    "FAIL_ON_4XX": "false"
  }
}

Notes
	•	Duplicate detection / Sessions are configured on the queue/topic in the portal (not in this code).
	•	The function throws on 408/429/5xx so the runtime will retry and eventually dead‑letter (based on Max delivery count).
	•	For 4xx errors, default is to log and complete (no retry) to avoid poison loops; set FAIL_ON_4XX=true if you’d rather dead‑letter via retries.

