Why this is “production‑grade”
	•	Thread‑safe singletons: one HttpClient shared across invocations.
	•	Config‑driven: URL/method/timeouts/headers via app settings (no code changes).
	•	Back‑pressure friendly: transient HTTP errors bubble up → Functions retry.
	•	Idempotency‑friendly: preserves CorrelationId from Service Bus if present; your Message API can use it.
	•	Minimal surface: The function doesn’t parse your payload at all (you can add parsing later when the contract is fixed).

